<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Privacy Policy - Spank App</title>
    <style>
        :root {
            --primary-color: #00CCFF;
            --secondary-color: #FF00FF;
            --bg-color: #0B0B0B;
            --card-bg: #1A1A1A;
            --text-color: #E0E0E0;
            --accent-glow: rgba(0, 204, 255, 0.2);
        }

        body {
            font-family: 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.6;
            color: var(--text-color);
            background-color: var(--bg-color);
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }

        .container {
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 40px auto;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        header {
            text-align: center;
            padding-bottom: 40px;
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--card-bg);
        }

        h1 {
            color: var(--primary-color);
            font-size: 2.5rem;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 2px;
        }

        h2 {
            color: var(--secondary-color);
            border-left: 4px solid var(--secondary-color);
            padding-left: 15px;
            margin-top: 40px;
        }

        .last-updated {
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            color: #888;
        }

        section {
            background: var(--card-bg);
            padding: 25px;
            border-radius: 12px;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);
            border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.05);
        }

        .sensor-tag {
            display: inline-block;
            background: var(--accent-glow);
            color: var(--primary-color);
            padding: 4px 12px;
            border-radius: 20px;
            font-size: 0.85rem;
            font-weight: bold;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

        ul {
            padding-left: 20px;
        }

        li {
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

        footer {
            text-align: center;
            margin-top: 60px;
            padding: 20px;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            color: #666;
        }

        a {
            color: var(--primary-color);
            text-decoration: none;
        }

        a:hover {
            text-decoration: underline;
        }

        @media (max-width: 600px) {
            .container {
                margin: 10px auto;
                padding: 15px;
            }
            h1 { font-size: 1.8rem; }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="container">
    <header>
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p><strong>App:</strong> Spank</p>
        <p><strong>Developer:</strong> Däniel Ebrahimzadeh AI Labs</p>
        <p class="last-updated">Effective Date: May 20, 2024</p>
    </header>

    <section id="introduction">
        <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
        <p>Welcome to Spank, an interactive motion-based prank application. Däniel Ebrahimzadeh AI Labs ("we," "us," or "our") is committed to protecting your privacy. This policy explains how we handle technical data and user-provided information to provide a safe and transparent experience.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="data-collection">
        <h2>2. Types of Data Collected</h2>
        <p>We distinguish between data processed automatically for app functionality and data provided voluntarily by the user.</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Automatic Technical Data:</strong> High-frequency sensor data required for real-time motion detection.</li>
            <li><strong>Voluntary User Data:</strong> Audio recordings created via the "Community Voice" feature and contact information provided during support requests.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="sensor-usage">
        <h2>3. Detailed Sensor Usage</h2>
        
        <div>
            <span class="sensor-tag">ACCELEROMETER</span>
            <p>Spank uses the device's accelerometer to detect physical impact and motion intensity. This data is processed <strong>locally in real-time</strong> on your device's CPU/NPU. We do not store, log, or transmit accelerometer patterns to any external servers.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="margin-top: 20px;">
            <span class="sensor-tag">MICROPHONE</span>
            <p>The microphone is used <strong>only</strong> when you explicitly interact with the "Record" button in the Community Voice section. 
            <ul>
                <li>Audio is recorded into a temporary local file.</li>
                <li>Transmission to our servers only occurs if you choose to "Submit" the recording.</li>
                <li>Background recording is strictly prohibited and technically impossible within our implementation.</li>
            </ul>
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="retention">
        <h2>4. Data Retention & Deletion</h2>
        <p>Your privacy is maintained through minimal retention:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Motion Data:</strong> Deleted immediately after the audio trigger is processed (milliseconds).</li>
            <li><strong>Local Audio:</strong> Custom recordings stay on your device unless the app is uninstalled or data is cleared.</li>
            <li><strong>Submitted Audio:</strong> If you submit a voice file, it is stored on our secure servers for review. You may request deletion at any time by contacting us.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="children">
        <h2>5. Children's Privacy (COPPA/GDPR-K)</h2>
        <p>Spank is not intended for children under the age of 13 (or 16 in the EU). We do not knowingly collect data from children. If we discover a child has submitted audio data, we will delete it immediately from our servers.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="security">
        <h2>6. Security Measures</h2>
        <p>We employ industry-standard encryption (TLS/SSL) for any data in transit. As a "Purely Native" implementation, we avoid third-party SDKs, significantly reducing the "attack surface" and ensuring your data isn't shared with advertising networks or data brokers.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="user-rights">
        <h2>7. Your Rights (GDPR Compliant)</h2>
        <p>Under GDPR and similar global regulations, you have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Access any data you have submitted to us.</li>
            <li>Request the permanent deletion of your submitted recordings.</li>
            <li>Withdraw consent for microphone usage via system settings at any time.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="contact">
        <h2>8. Contact Information</h2>
        <p>For privacy inquiries, data deletion requests, or support, please contact:</p>
        <p>
            <strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:mh.ebrz@gmail.com">mh.ebrz@gmail.com</a><br>
            <strong>Web:</strong> <a href="https://mhe931.github.io/" target="_blank">mhe931.github.io</a>
        </p>
    </section>

    <footer>
        &copy; 2024 Däniel Ebrahimzadeh AI Labs. All rights reserved.<br>
        This policy is subject to updates to remain compliant with evolving App Store and Play Store guidelines.
    </footer>
</div>

</body>
</html>
